<subSubSection id="B434D34B8A7C756FD16D01C2A6FE011A" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="differential diagnosis">
<paragraph id="A56C9D79EEB1B29EDA4D00C4B591457A" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Differential diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="67C0101627954911F3BBB56D6F3196D3" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<taxonomicName id="D194D4706AC4C2E6722E3486D32AE55B" authority="Mayr, 1861" authorityName="Salata, Borowiec &amp; Trichas" authorityYear="2018" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Temnothorax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Temnothorax ikarosi" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ikarosi">
<emphasis id="987AF17AC8708D3E4061EA2B4C5407BB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Temnothorax ikarosi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="B5A7E6ED1E21A5181CA035595D233863" genus="T." lsidName="T. parnonensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="parnonensis">
<emphasis id="BB1163FCC3D60D4AF85F01A84E540E02" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">T. parnonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in entirely sculptured head and frons lacking smooth patches; from 
<taxonomicName id="BF338EA52880F3461B493BBBB0F4956F" genus="T." lsidName="T. euboeae" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="euboeae">
<emphasis id="71A664C14CFFE203FFE1A9FD76528CD5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">T. euboeae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it differs in elongated petiolar peduncle and triangular propodeal spines; from 
<taxonomicName id="7C9F50BA8808023CB7591071F1C44725" genus="T." lsidName="T. anodontoides" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="anodontoides">
<emphasis id="996B63FA235C816F72E6AFDEEB56E5E6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">T. anodontoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it differs in presence of distinct propodeal spines; from 
<taxonomicName id="D1ACAC5A1F219331C78288EBC1FC0A04" genus="T." lsidName="T. arkasi" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="arkasi">
<emphasis id="1E64BA7AD1488050209C3F17CD4802AD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">T. arkasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it differs in less elongate head, sparser and thicker promesonotal sculpture and bigger propodeal spines.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
